# Project: Eiken Learning App

## Overview
- Django app for Eiken study (grammar, reading, listening, progress tracking).
- Core apps: `accounts`, `exams`, `questions`.
- Local dev uses SQLite by default; production uses PostgreSQL on Fly.io.

## Architecture
- Routing and project settings: `eiken_project/`.
- Exam and user-facing flow: `exams/`.
- Question registration and data maintenance: `questions/management/commands/`.
- Source question files: `data/questions/`.
- Utility scripts for PDF/audio: `utils/`.

## Working Style
- Prefer small, practical changes that match existing Django patterns.
- Keep backward compatibility for existing question text formats and management commands.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions for simple view/model updates.

## Data and Content Safety
- Never commit secrets or credentials.
- When changing question import flow, verify:
  - parsing still works for current text files in `data/questions/`
  - related audio/image paths remain valid
  - corresponding pages in `exams/templates/exams/` still render

## Verification
- Before finishing, run practical checks when possible:
  - `python manage.py check`
  - `python manage.py test` (or focused tests)
- If command changes are included, run the affected command with a safe subset/dry-run path if available.

## Deployment Awareness
- Fly settings are in `config/` and root deployment files.
- `scripts/start.sh` runs `collectstatic` and `migrate` before `gunicorn`; keep changes compatible.
